# Available Tools

This document describes the tools available to nanobot.
It is injected into the system prompt to help the agent understand its capabilities.

---

## File Operations

### read_file
Read the contents of a file.

### write_file
Write content to a file (creates parent directories if needed).
Set `append=true` to append instead of overwrite.

### edit_file
Edit a file by replacing specific text.

### list_dir
List contents of a directory.

---

## Shell Execution

### exec
Execute a shell command and return output.

**Notes:**
- Commands have a configurable timeout (default 60s)
- Dangerous commands are blocked (rm -rf, format, dd, shutdown, etc.)
- Use `restrictToWorkspace` config to sandbox file access

---

## Web Access

### web_search
Search the web using Brave Search API.
Requires `tools.web.search.apiKey` in config.

### web_fetch
Fetch and extract main content from a URL.
Supports markdown or plain text extraction.

---

## Communication

### message
Send a message to the user (used by background tasks and cron jobs).

---

## Background Tasks

### spawn
Spawn a subagent to handle a task in the background.
Use for complex or time-consuming tasks that can run independently.

---

## Scheduled Tasks (Cron)

### cron
Create, list, or remove scheduled tasks.

```
cron(action="add", message="Good morning!", cron_expr="0 9 * * *")
cron(action="add", message="Take a break", every_seconds=3600)
cron(action="list")
cron(action="remove", job_id="abc123")
```

---

## Heartbeat Task Management

Edit `HEARTBEAT.md` to add or remove periodic background tasks.
The file is checked every 30 minutes — tasks with `- [ ]` are executed.

---

*For developer docs on adding custom tools, see ARCHITECTURE.md.*
